建议直接加入：

```text
The present evidence has three important limits. First, the system is hybrid optical-digital: reconstruction is performed by a digital ridge stage whose degrees of freedom exceed those of the phase-only optical frontend. Second, the natural-image experiments use project-local proxy subsets rather than licensed benchmark-root ImageNet or COCO images. Third, the tolerance results are simulation-based and show unresolved failure under 2 px lateral phase-mask displacement. These limits do not invalidate the controlled dual-ledger benchmark, but they bound the scope of claims about natural-image deployment and hardware implementation.
